    "summary": "Karin Arink was born in Delft (NL), lived for a few years as a child in Boston Massachusetts, as a teenager in London, did an exchange to Frankfurt-am-Main and later a year residency in Kitakyushu Japan. \nShe studied in Rotterdam and at the Rijksakademie Amsterdam, and won 1st Prize Prix de Rome Sculpture in 1992. \nKarin Arink exhibits extensively both in Holland and abroad, e.g. in Stedelijk Museum Schiedam, Van Abbemuseum, Centraal Museum Utrecht, Museum Boijmans van Beuningen, Kasteel Oud-Rekem, Gerhard Marcks Haus Bremen, Museo Pecci and Stichting De Pont Tilburg. \n\nShe writes, is advisor in various committees and jurys; and collaborates a.o. as member of Foundation B.a.d Rotterdam. \nLecturer and Course Leader BA Fine Art and Photography at the Willem de Kooning Academy Rotterdam.",
